  "text": "To reveal the β1Int-HaloTag protein subcellular localization, we combined the HaloTag technology and the permeabilization agent digitonin [CITATION_1] . Cells were cotransfected with β1Int-HaloTag and GFP, and then labeled with the HaloTag TMR ligand (Figure 3c ). Coexpression of the proteins is shown by the yellow overlay ( Figure 3d ). Digitonin treatment permeabilized the membrane, which allowed freely floating GFP to diffuse out of the cell over time while internally bound β1Int-HaloTag was retained in the cell, presumably by cellular transport and recycling machinery (Figure 3c, d ). This result shows that the HaloTag fusion did not affect normal processing of a membrane bound protein, and that the HaloTag tech- nology can be used to distinguish free floating and membrane bound proteins.",
